{"word":"ἄμετρος","slug":"ἄμετρος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄμετρος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μέτρον'><el>μέτρον</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>without measure, immense, excessive, boundless</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>ἀμέτρως</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>ἄμετρα</el> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <b><a href='S:Babrius'>Babr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>immoderate</i>, in moral sense, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>ἀμέτρως</el>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}